on android, vim /system/usr/keylayout/Generic.kl
key 58 CTRL_LEFT

on linux, 
su
dumpkeys > key.map
vim key.map
keycode 58 = Control
loadkeys key.map
then re-login, it will work

for tty
write it in .bashrc
vim ~/.bashrc
sudo loadkeys $HOME/key.map
to revert
loadkeys -d

for Xorg
vim .xinitrc, put this at the first, 'cause fvwm will stuck at the end
setxkbmap -layout us -option ctrl:nocaps
xmodmap won't use ~/.Xmodmap on archlinux 

sudo localectl set-x11-keymap "" "" "" ctrl:swapcaps
to reverse
sudo localectl set-x11-keymap "" "" "" ctrl:ctrl
sudo localectl set-x11-keymap "" "" "" capslock:capslock
killall Xorg and exit, then login again
localectl will create /etc/X11/xorg.conf.d/00-keyboard.conf
or just sudo rm /etc/X11/xorg.conf.d/00-keyboard.conf
https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Xorg/Keyboard_configuration#Using_localectl


